  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nSSZ List items are to be prepended with 4 bytes to show the length.\r\nShould Address, Bitfield, PublicKey, Hash256, and Signature, AggregateSiganture have the length prepended?\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nCurrently the following prepend the length bytes:\r\n- Bitfield (N bytes)\r\n- Signature (96 bytes)\r\n- AggregateSignature (96 bytes)\r\n- PublicKey (48 bytes)\r\n\r\nWhile the following types do not prepend length:\r\n- Hash256 (32 bytes)\r\n- Address (20 bytes)\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nMy interpretation is that all of the types should have the lengths prepended. \r\nSee https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/issues/837 for a final answer.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nFollowing an answer to the above either add or remove length to the ssz encoding/decoding if required.",
