    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The verdict is that any types with a fixed number of bytes can be considered tuples hence do not prepend the length e.g. Signatures, Addresses,...\r\nThose with a variable number of bytes e.g. Bitfield will require the length to be prepended.\r\n\r\n# TODO\r\nRemove encoding/decoding of length from\r\n- Signature\r\n- Aggregate Signature\r\n- PublicKey\r\n- Any other types with fixed number of bytes\r\nEnsure Bitfield and other variable length objects have length prepended.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      ",
